        "title": "feat(workboard): add agent coordination tools",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Add Workboard agent coordination tools for listing, reading, claiming, heartbeating, releasing, commenting, proving, and unblocking cards.\n- Persist coordination metadata for claims, artifacts, diagnostics, and notifications, with diagnostics refresh, claim-token redaction, bounded worker context, and UI badges/events.\n- Document the Workboard agent workflow and add locale coverage for new Workboard UI strings.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm test ui/src/i18n/test/translate.test.ts extensions/browser/src/cli/browser-cli-actions-input/register.element.test.ts extensions/workboard/src/store.test.ts extensions/workboard/src/gateway.test.ts extensions/workboard/src/tools.test.ts ui/src/ui/controllers/workboard.test.ts ui/src/ui/views/workboard.test.ts`\n- `env -u OPENCLAW_TESTBOX pnpm check:changed`\n- `/Users/steipete/Projects/agent-scripts/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Workboard can now coordinate agent-owned card work with claims, heartbeats, release, proof/artifact handoff, diagnostics, and UI visibility.\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw checkout on macOS using repo Vitest, all-lane changed-check, and local autoreview.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Focused UI/i18n/browser/Workboard tests, all-lane `check:changed`, and autoreview local mode.\nEvidence after fix: Focused tests passed 107 UI files plus browser and Workboard shards; `check:changed` passed package guards, typecheck, lint, and import cycles; autoreview reported no accepted/actionable findings.\nObserved result after fix: Claim tokens are redacted on read/list surfaces, scoped mutations validate against latest claim state inside queued writes, diagnostics clear when resolver actions occur, and worker context includes artifact handoff data.\nWhat was not tested: No live dashboard browser session or multi-process external plugin install was run; coverage is local unit/integration plus package/lock/type/lint gates.\n",
